      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 4S utilizes the iconic wide-body chassis and braking system derived from the Turbo, paired with a high-revving 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six. The M96 powerplant features VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, delivering a linear power band through the 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is prioritized, with a documented history addressing the IMS bearing and rear main seal to ensure long-term reliability of the reciprocating assembly. The suspension geometry maintains factory-spec kinematics, offering precise turn-in and controlled damping. Equipped with four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors, the braking system provides excellent heat dissipation and firm pedal modulation. This is a driver-focused example with a robust drivetrain, ready for immediate high-performance applications.",
